  "source": "[\\product:of{m}:and{n}]\nDefines: p is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nwhen: m, n is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\nexpresses:\n. \\product:of{m}:and{\\set.theoretic.zero} = \\set.theoretic.zero\n. forAll: k is \\set.theoretic.natural.number\n  then: \\product:of{m}:and{\\set.theoretic.successor{k}} = \\sum:of{\\product:of{m}:and{k}}:and{m}\nDocumented:\n. called: \"product of $m?$ and $n?$\"\n. written: \"m? \\cdot n?\"\n. description: \"The product $m \\cdot n$, defined by recursion on $n$: $m \\cdot 0 = 0$ and $m \\cdot n^+ = m \\cdot n + m$. Multiplication is the binary operation given by $\\cdot$.\"\nId: \"24bdd310-86f4-4c1c-a44d-c850304d6d49\"",
